ExactMatch@N is a straightforward metric for evaluating generative models like Smart Compose.

Here's a simple and short explanation for your notes:

ExactMatch@N

Measures how often a generated suggestion exactly matches the 
first N words of the actual (ground truth) text. 
It's calculated as the percentage of suggestions 
where this exact match occurs.

N: The specific number of words you're checking for an exact match.
Higher score: Means the model is better at predicting the exact next N words.

Example (ExactMatch@3):
Ground Truth: "I hope you are doing well."
Suggestion 1: "I hope you are fantastic."
First 3 words: "I hope you" (Matches "I hope you" from ground truth) -> Match!
Suggestion 2: "I hope to see you."
First 3 words: "I hope to" (Does NOT match "I hope you" from ground truth) -> No Match!
If these were the only two suggestions, the ExactMatch@3 score would be 1/2 = 0.50 (or 50%).